    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="483"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 13329/4–5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 309.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    the department’s telegram of the 1st instant,<note n="1" xml:id="d483fn1"
                        >Supra.</note> and to inclose herewith copy of note which I to-day
                    personally handed to the minister for foreign affairs concerning the matter.
                    Count Hayashi, in the course of the interview which I had with him, begged me to
                    transmit to the department the Japanese Government’s deep appreciation and
                    thanks for the message of sympathy.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. J. O’Brien.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Minister for Foreign Affairs</gloss>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-02">
                                <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1908</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 105.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Monsieur le Ministre</hi>: I am this moment in receipt
                        of a cablegram from the Secretary of State asking me to convey the sympathy
                        of the President and Government of the United States with the Japanese
                        Government in the terrible disaster resulting from the explosion on the <hi
                            rend="italic">Matsushima</hi>. In performing this office, I desire to
                        give expression to my own sincere regret for the sad occurrence and my
                        genuine sympathy with those to whom it has brought loss and sorrow.</p>
                    <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. J. O’Brien.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
